    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">British Columbia, particularly the Abbotsford region, is home to some of Canada’s most productive specialty crop farms. From berries and mushrooms to niche vegetables, local farmers produce high-quality, delicate crops that require careful handling to reach markets both locally and internationally.</p>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-10">In today’s competitive agriculture landscape, producing quality crops is only part of the challenge. Ensuring that these crops arrive fresh, intact, and visually appealing is equally critical. Smart packaging solutions—such as trays, baskets, and totes from Pacific Injection Molding—are essential for protecting delicate specialty crops while optimizing labor, storage, and transport efficiency.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">The Role of Packaging in Specialty Crop Success</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Specialty crops are particularly sensitive due to their size, fragility, and perishability. Proper packaging is crucial for several reasons:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-8">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Protection from Damage</span>: Delicate produce like mushrooms, berries, and small vegetables can easily be bruised or crushed. Packaging designed to cushion and separate crops prevents losses.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Shelf-Life Extension</span>: Adequate airflow, moisture control, and insulation help extend the freshness of perishable products.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Operational Efficiency</span>: Ergonomically designed trays and baskets facilitate handling, stacking, and transport from field to processing facilities.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Visual Appeal</span>: Attractive packaging communicates quality and professionalism, enhancing marketability and consumer satisfaction.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">In essence, packaging is not just a container—it is an investment in crop quality, farm profitability, and customer satisfaction.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Pacific Injection Molding Specialty Packaging Products</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Pacific Injection Molding provides a wide array of specialty packaging products tailored to meet the needs of BC farmers and exporters:</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4.5” Harvest Trays (Tan)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Ideal for small crops such as delicate herbs, microgreens, or specialty berries, these trays offer stackability and ventilation, reducing damage and spoilage during harvest and transport.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Half Bushel Baskets (Red)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Designed for medium-sized harvests, these baskets are lightweight yet durable, allowing workers to carry significant volumes without strain. Their bright red color also aids in farm sorting and organization.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Mushroom Trays (Blue)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Mushrooms are exceptionally delicate, and blue mushroom trays from Pacific Injection Molding provide the perfect combination of airflow, cushioning, and stackability. They help maintain shape and quality during both storage and shipping.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Recycling Trays (Blue)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Sustainability is increasingly important for specialty crop producers. Reusable recycling trays allow farms to adopt eco-friendly practices while maintaining efficiency during harvest and distribution.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Mini Berry Trays (Red)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Compact and visually appealing, mini berry trays are perfect for retail-ready servings. Their ergonomic design ensures berries remain intact while making them easy to stack and transport.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Non-Divided Berry Trays (Green)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">These trays accommodate larger quantities of berries while maintaining structural integrity, protecting the fruit from crushing and ensuring proper airflow.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Divided Berry Trays (Green)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Divided trays separate individual berries or small clusters, preventing bruising and enhancing visual presentation. These are ideal for premium markets or direct-to-consumer sales.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Large Solid Wall Agricultural Totes (White)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Designed for bulk storage, these totes handle heavier crops like squash, carrots, or potatoes. Their solid walls protect produce during transport, while stackable designs maximize space efficiency.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Small Ventilated Agricultural Totes (Green/Orange)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Perfect for delicate crops, these totes offer optimal airflow to prevent moisture buildup, maintaining freshness from field to market.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Large Ventilated Agricultural Totes (Lime Green)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">Ideal for long-distance transport and export, these totes combine durability with ventilation, protecting sensitive crops while facilitating efficient stacking and handling.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Milk Crates</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">Pacific Injection Molding also provides a variety of milk crates suitable for niche agricultural products, such as small bottles, dairy items, or liquid-based specialty crops. These crates are stackable, durable, and color-coded for efficient sorting and handling.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Assorted Specialty Trays</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">Additional offerings such as 4.5” harvest trays, half bushel baskets, mushroom trays, and recycling trays provide flexible solutions for farms of all sizes, supporting diverse crop types and harvest volumes.</p>

