    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Design Considerations for Specialty Crop Packaging</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">When selecting packaging solutions, BC farmers should consider:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Crop Sensitivity</span>: Delicate crops require cushioned, ventilated trays to prevent bruising and moisture buildup.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Stackability</span>: Properly designed trays and totes save storage space and prevent damage when stacked.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Ergonomics</span>: Lightweight and handle-friendly designs reduce labor strain during harvest and transport.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Color Coding</span>: Using different colored trays and totes improves sorting, reduces errors, and enhances operational efficiency.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Sustainability</span>: Reusable trays and totes support environmentally conscious practices, aligning with consumer and regulatory expectations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Color Coding for Farm Efficiency</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">Color-coded trays make sorting and handling easier:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Red Trays</span>: Small berries or specialty fruits</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Green Trays</span>: Leafy greens and vegetables</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Blue Trays</span>: Mushrooms and delicate crops</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Tan Trays</span>: Microgreens or specialty herbs</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Operational Tips for Specialty Crop Packaging</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">To maximize the effectiveness of packaging solutions, farmers should adopt best practices:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Pre-Cool Crops Before Packaging</span>: Maintaining optimal temperatures preserves freshness.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Avoid Overfilling Trays or Totes</span>: Overfilled containers can crush produce at the bottom.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Inspect Trays Regularly</span>: Check for cracks, warping, or wear to ensure durability.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Implement a Rotation System</span>: Rotate older trays first to maintain consistent wear.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Train Staff on Handling Techniques</span>: Proper loading, stacking, and transport reduce damage and improve efficiency.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Sustainability and Environmental Benefits</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Smart packaging solutions, such as reusable trays and totes, significantly reduce environmental impact. Benefits include:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li>Lower dependence on single-use packaging</li>
      <li>Reduced plastic and cardboard waste</li>
      <li>Support for eco-friendly farming practices</li>
      <li>Enhanced brand reputation among environmentally conscious consumers</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">Sustainability is increasingly important in Canadian agriculture, and farms that adopt reusable packaging demonstrate responsibility and leadership in the market.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Future Trends in Specialty Crop Packaging</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">As the BC agriculture sector evolves, packaging trends are advancing:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Smart Packaging</span>: QR codes or sensors for tracking produce quality during transport.</li>
